					<span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/drclef" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(213153); return false;"  ><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=213153&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1610227371" alt="DrClef" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=213153)"/></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/drclef" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(213153); return false;" >DrClef</a></span> <span class="odate time_1389527837 format_%25e%20%25b%20%25Y%2C%20%25H%3A%25M%7Cagohover">12 Jan 2014 11:57</span>
														</div>
			</div>
			<div class="content" id="post-content-1934030">
									

<p>Schifter,</p>
<p>I made some changes to your entry to better fit the tone of the rest of the page and bring it better into line with the way the GOC does things. A few things to note:</p>
<p>D.C. al Fine is the head of the entire GOC. Having her talk about the UHEC system and give advice to individual operatives is like the President of the U.S. giving combat advice to an Army tank crew. But I liked the idea of getting a personal perspective on things, so I'm reusing Agent Madrigal from the field guides.</p>
<p>Your FEDS system kind of exists, but in the form of a roomsweeper mine used by Strike teams in whitesuits. I made it clear that this is a scaled up version of the same. I did that as well to a few other systems that are clearly scaled up from White Suits.</p>
<p>Lastly&#8230; &quot;flame-based weaponry&quot; is a pet peeve of mine. Just say flamethrower. Not that people use them much these days: too heavy, too many nasty side effects (flamethrower operators are notorious for passing out or getting light headed due to fumes and lack of oxygen caused by combustion). They're still useful for burning down undergrowth, but the only people who use them in combat these days are lunatics, and video game heroes.</p>
<p>Tangential note: flamethrowers are considered illegal under &quot;Prohibitions or Restrictions on the Use of Incendiary Weapons (Protocol III).&quot;. The GOC would therefore be forbidden from using them on humans.</p>

							</div>

								
					
