					<span class="printuser deleted" data-id="1718084"><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/common--images/avatars/default/a16.png" alt=""/>(account deleted)</span> <span class="odate time_1389533310 format_%25e%20%25b%20%25Y%2C%20%25H%3A%25M%7Cagohover">12 Jan 2014 13:28</span>
														</div>
			</div>
			<div class="content" id="post-content-1934069">
									

<p>Nooooo that silly &quot;FEDS&quot; abbreviation that I was so proud of! Also, I don't know if you realize, but a light tank made out of buckypaper would only weigh about a couple hundred kilograms. It has to do with carbon nanotubes having a weight to strength ratio about 500 times better than that of steel. 14 tonnes = 48,000 kilos / 500 = 96 kilograms. Most of the real weight would probably come from the ceramic and the gelatin. Probably amount to maybe&#8230; half a ton? A ton tops, and that's no bipedal machine, thats a damned thick suit. If it were a huge bipedal machine, it would be a vehicle.</p>
<p>Imagine a big stone golem, making the the most god awful screech, charging at you with a <em>very</em> big gun. I suppose with good enough servomotors, it could go bashing through walls, although the shock absorbent gel would make it hard&#8230; Pavement would probably only crack or something. Is it okay if I touch up the thing a bit? I wasn't really going for a gundam here.</p>
<p>Oh, and I'm going to start working on a sub aquatic suit, then maybe a railgun, then a superimposed load weapon, then&#8230; I don't know. My precognition doesn't go that far into the future. Anyways, don't use the color blue.</p>

							</div>

								
