					<span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/thedeadlymoose" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(732274); return false;"  ><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=732274&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1610227372" alt="thedeadlymoose" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=732274)"/></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/thedeadlymoose" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(732274); return false;" >thedeadlymoose</a></span> <span class="odate time_1426471618 format_%25e%20%25b%20%25Y%2C%20%25H%3A%25M%7Cagohover">16 Mar 2015 02:06</span>
														</div>
			</div>
			<div class="content" id="post-content-2251446">
									

<p>Suggestion: Include more description on VERITAS headpieces. Actually more description on VERITAS &#8212; strengths, weaknesses, etc &#8212; would be interesting.</p>
<p>There's also an interesting potential issue here&#8230; one of &quot;balance&quot;. The White Suit in particular has this issue; I like the agent's note, but besides the fact that it's uncomfortable (good detail), it's just a generic super suit. The Grey Suit is more interesting.</p>
<p>Oddly, the more powerful Orange Suit works better, if only because of the presentation: it seems, well, really memorable, and the agent's note makes it clear they're <em>not</em> invincible, but seem so. They're a little over-powered, but they also seem fairly rare and like something that would be entertaining to use in a story.</p>

							</div>

								
					
